125	1	2013-06-21 12:49:23	2013-06-21 04:49:23.102285	<p>These were the speakers of <a href="http://nyc.org.ph/nyc-2012/" target="_blank">NYC 2012</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<span>\r\n    <img src="http://nyc.org.ph/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Noel-del-Castillo.jpg" alt="Noel del Castillo" width="150" height="240" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-171" />\r\n    <h2 style="display: inline">Noel del Castillo</h2>\r\n</span>\r\n<p>Mr. del Castillo graduated from the UP Diliman School of Economics (UPSE) in 2006 and his Master of Arts in Economics in 2011. While doing his graduate studies, he was a teaching fellow at the UPSE, teaching several introductory economic theory classes in the undergraduate level. For a few years, he served as an analyst for the Philippine Stock Exchange. In 2010, he was one of the 25 participants in the Ronald Coase Institute Workshop held in Shanghai, an international workshop that gathers young economists and social scientists in formulating new institutional economic theory. There, he studied the importance of regulations such as the Securities Regulation Code in strengthening financial institutions like the stock market. Today, he serves as a lecturer in economics at Miriam College.</p>\r\n\r\n<span>\r\n    <img src="http://nyc.org.ph/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Solita-Monsod.jpg" alt="Solita Monsod" width="150" height="240" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-173" />\r\n    <h2 style="display: inline">Solita Collas-Monsod</h2>\r\n    <em>Download</em>: <a href="http://nyc.org.ph/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Solita-Monsod-MDGs-Made-Easy.ppt">Solita Monsod - MDG's Made Easy</a>\r\n</span>\r\n<p>Mrs. Monsod, popularly known as “Mareng Winnie," is an academician, media personality, public servant, and deemed one of the top economists of the country. She obtained her Bachelor of Science in Economics at the UPSE, graduating cum laude, and her Master of the Arts and Ph.D. in Economics at the University of Pensylvania, completing all her requirements for the latter except her dissertation. She began teaching at the UPSE in 1971 and is today a professor emerita. Specializing in development economics, she has worked extensively in government, serving as National Economic Development Advisory (NEDA) Director-General from 1986-1989 and at various agencies of the United Nations. Mrs. Monsod is probably best known for her television shows, which include <em>Bawal ang Pasaway</em> and <em>Unang Hirit</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<span>\r\n    <img src="http://nyc.org.ph/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Benjamin-Diokno.jpg" alt="Benjamin Diokno" width="150" height="240" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-176" />\r\n    <h2 style="display: inline">Benjamin E. Diokno</h2>\r\n    <em>Download</em>: <a href="http://nyc.org.ph/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Benjamin-Diokno-Where-Do-We-Go-From-Here.ppt">Benjamin Diokno - Where Do We Go From Here</a>\r\n</span>\r\n<p>Dr. Diokno graduated with a BA in Public Administration as his undergraduate degree and an MA in Public Administration as his masteral degree. After receiving a Certificate in Developmental Economics in the UPSE under a University of Wisconsin program, he continued his pursuit of economics by obtaining graduate degrees in Economics from the UPSE and in Political Economy at Johns Hopkins University, as well as a Ph.D. in Economics from Syracuse University in New York. Dr. Diokno served as Budget Secretary from 1998-2001 and has worked with the Asian Development Bank (ADB), the European Commission, the United States Agency for International Development (USAID), and the government of Cambodia. Besides teaching, he is a columnist for <em>Business World</em> and <em>Malaya Business Insight</em>.</p>	Speakers		publish	closed	open		speakers			2013-07-29 04:36:35	2013-07-28 20:36:35		40	http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=125	2	page		0
