110	1	2013-06-21 05:54:41	2013-06-20 21:54:41	<p>Here are some common questions high schools ask regarding NYC. Need further clarifications? Don’t hesitate to email our External Relations team at <a href="mailto:er@nyc.org.ph" target="_blank">er@nyc.org.ph</a>!</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>How do we participate in NYC?</strong></h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>\r\n        Express your intention to join through:<ul>\r\n            <li>Text: 0917-536-3402</li>\r\n            <li>Email: <a href="mailto:er@nyc.org.ph" target="_blank">er@nyc.org.ph</a></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        Accomplish/submit the following requirements:<ul>\r\n            <li>Registration fee<span style="color: red">*</span></li>\r\n            <li>Participant's Form</li>\r\n            <li>Educator's Form</li>\r\n            <li>Scanned copy of deposit slip</li>\r\n        </ul\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>Requirements are due on or before <strong>August 9, 2013</strong></li>\r\n    <li>Send your student representatives with the accompanying faculty members to the designated vanue on <strong>August 30 and/or August 31</strong>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="color: red">*</span><em>If you submit your requirements before <strong>August 9</strong>, you may avail of a special Php30 discount per delegate and a premium in the seating arrangements.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>How many delegates can we send?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Each school may send a <strong>minimum of five (5)</strong> and a <strong>maximum of eight (8)</strong> participants for the congress and a <strong>maximum of two (2)</strong> members of the administration or faculty.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>What is the difference between the single day option and the overnight option?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The congress proper takes place on the day of August 31, 2013. However, we understand that some of our participants will be coming from different regions and a single-day affair may not be worth the trip, so we offer an overnight option where the delegates will avail of hotel accommodations on the night of August 30.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To make the overnight option even more enticing, there will be a pre-event talk and dinner held exclusively for them. Transportation shall be provided from the hotel to the NYC venue for the following day, though schools may make their own transportation arrangements.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>My high school is not in Luzon. Can I still participate?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Though the NYC to date has never had participants from outside Luzon due to the understandable logistical difficulties, we still maintain that our invitation extends to <em>all</em> DepEd-accredited high schools in the Philippines. We embrace challenges, so if you’re an interested school from Palawan, Visayas, or Mindanao, send us an email at <a href="mailto:er@nyc.org.ph" target="_blank">er@nyc.org.ph</a> and let’s work something out!</p>	FAQ		inherit	open	open		92-revision-6			2013-06-21 05:54:41	2013-06-20 21:54:41		92	http://localhost/wordpress/92-revision-6/	0	revision		0
