94	1	2013-06-21 12:33:43	2013-06-21 04:33:43	<p>Here are some common questions high schools ask regarding NYC. Need further clarifications? Don’t hesitate to email our External Relations team at <a href="mailto:er@nyc.org.ph" target="_blank">er@nyc.org.ph</a>!</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>How do we participate in NYC?</strong></h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>\r\n        Express your intention to join through:<ul>\r\n            <li>Text: 0917-536-3402</li>\r\n            <li>Email: <a href="mailto:er@nyc.org.ph" target="_blank">er@nyc.org.ph</a></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        Accomplish/submit the following requirements:<ul>\r\n            <li>Registration fee<span style="color: red">*</span></li>\r\n            <li>Participant's Form</li>\r\n            <li>Educator's Form</li>\r\n            <li>Scanned copy of deposit slip</li>\r\n        </ul\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>Requirements are due on or before <strong>August 9, 2013</strong></li>\r\n    <li>Send your student representatives with the accompanying faculty members to the designated vanue on <strong>August 30 and/or August 31</strong>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="color: red">*</span><em>If you submit your requirements before <strong>August 9</strong>, you may avail of a special Php30 discount per delegate and a premium in the seating arrangements.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>How many delegates can we send?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Each school may send a <strong>minimum of five (5)</strong> and a <strong>maximum of eight (8)</strong> participants for the congress and a <strong>maximum of two (2)</strong> members of the administration or faculty.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>What is the difference between the single day option and the overnight option?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The congress proper takes place on the day of August 31, 2013. However, we understand that some of our participants will be coming from different regions and a single-day affair may not be worth the trip, so we offer an overnight option where the delegates will avail of hotel accommodations on the night of August 30.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To make the overnight option even more enticing, there will be a pre-event talk and dinner held exclusively for them. Transportation shall be provided from the hotel to the NYC venue for the following day, though schools may make their own transportation arrangements.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>My high school is not in Luzon. Can I still participate?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Though the NYC to date has never had participants from outside Luzon due to the understandable logistical difficulties, we still maintain that our invitation extends to <em>all</em> DepEd-accredited high schools in the Philippines. We embrace challenges, so if you’re an interested school from Palawan, Visayas, or Mindanao, send us an email at <a href="mailto:er@nyc.org.ph" target="_blank">er@nyc.org.ph</a> and let’s work something out!</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Who will be responsible for the students during congress?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The organizing body of the National Youth Congress - composed of students from the UP School of Economics Student Council and the UP Economics Society - shall be responsible for the students during the duration of the whole congress. On the other hand, the organizers are not responsible for the students in events outside the congress. Each delegate is required to submit a waiver stating the latter.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>What if we cannot stay for the full duration of NYC? Will there be a discount in the participation fee?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We regret to say that you will still be charged the full fee regardless of how much of the congress you attend.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>When is the deadline for confirming attendance?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Deadline for confirmation is on or before <strong>August 9, 2013</strong>. If you pre-register and paythe entire amount of fees on or before <strong>August 9</strong>, you get a special discount of Php30 per delegate and a premium in the seating arrangement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For schools that confirm on or before <strong>July 31</strong> but opt not to pre-register, they will <em>not</em> have to pay the full fees yet. They are however required to submit a down payment worth 50% of the registration fee, plus an additional Php100 for overnight delegates. They will then have to pay the full amount by August 9.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please take not that late registrants and walk-ins shall be charged an extra fee.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>What do we need to bring?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n    For those availing the overnight option:\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>Clothes</li>\r\n        <li>Toiletries</li>\r\n        <li>Medication (if any)</li>\r\n        <li>Pocket money</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    <br />\r\n    For everyone:<ul>\r\n        <li>School ID</li>\r\n        <li>Other personal necessities</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n</p>	FAQ		inherit	open	open		92-autosave			2013-06-21 12:33:43	2013-06-21 04:33:43		92	http://localhost/wordpress/92-autosave/	0	revision		0
140	1	2013-06-23 18:36:10	2013-06-23 10:36:10	<p>The ninth installment of the National Youth Congress was held on August 31, 2012 at the P&G Room of the UP College of Business Administration and on September 1, 2012 at the GT-Toyota Asian Center Auditorium. Titled <em>Pedaling Towards Prosperity: The Pursuit for Progressive Development</em>, it focused on Philippine economic development.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NYC 2012 was notable for being the first to have participating high schools from Luzon, Visayas, and Mindanao. It was also the first not to be held at the UP School of Economics Auditorium, which was being renovated at the time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n    Click on the links below to learn more about NYC 2012:<ul>\r\n        <li><a href="poster">Poster</a></li>\r\n        <li><a href="schools">Schools</a></li>\r\n        <li><a href="speakers">Speakers</a></li>\r\n        <li><a href="organizer">Organizer</a></li>\r\n        <li><a href="pictures">Pictures</a></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n</p>	NYC 2012		inherit	open	open		40-revision-21			2013-06-23 18:36:10	2013-06-23 10:36:10		40	http://localhost/wordpress/40-revision-21/	0	revision		0
