-content/uploads/2013/06/EcoSoc-Logo.png" alt="EcoSoc Logo" width="150" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-163" />The <strong>UP Economics Society</strong> (UP Ecosoc) is a prominent student organization based in the University of the Philippines Diliman. Its founding in 1958 preceded the founding of its home college, the UP School of Economics, by eight years, which explains why its charter members are all from the College of Business Administration. Through its numerous and diverse activities, UP Ecosoc exhibits each of its three thrusts: <em>Service</em> in its outreach programs like medical missions and weekly daycare sessions, <em>Excellence</em> through its fundraising events like the <a href="http://www.facebook.com/upecosocmonth" target="_blank">Ecosoc Month parties</a>, <a href="http://www.facebook.com/musikapella" target="_blank">Musikapella</a>, and <a href="http://www.facebook.com/bandindemand" target="_blank">Band in Demand</a>, and <em>Tradition</em> through the shaping of its members into skilled, critical-minded individuals with a passion for using what they learn to give back to the country. The Society is centered around its Scholarship Fund, which, through the decades, have financially aided in the education of dozens of high school students.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Visit the UP Ecosoc website at <a href="http://upecosoc.org/" target="_blank">upecosoc.org</a> or its <a href="http://www.facebook.com/up.economics.society" target="_blank">Facebook page</a> to find out more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src="http://106.186.21.135/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/SESC.png" alt="SESC" width="150" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-164" />The <strong>UP School of Economics Student Council</strong> (SESC) is one of the most eminent student councils in the University. Representing students taking up BS Economics and BS Business Economics, the SESC works to promote the discipline of economics across the campus. It achieves this through its annual Economics Week, its participation in the <a href="http://www.facebook.com/JSSCP" target="_blank">Junior Social Scientists’ Conference of the Philippines</a> (JSSCP), and the release of informative pamphlets, like one regarding the <a href="http://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.228871173881530.37572.201782619923719&type=1" target="_blank">Oil Deregulation Law</a>. It also strives to maintain a camaraderie within the School of Economics by organizing bondings, sportsfests, and a varied wealth of other activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Connect with the SESC by liking their <a href="http://www.facebook.com/UPSE.StudentCouncil" target="_blank">Facebook page</a>.</p>	About		inherit	open	open		4-revision-24			2013-07-08 06:16:44	2013-07-07 22:16:44		4	http://106.186.21.135/wordpress/4-revision-24/	0	revision		0
